content:
{
  "plan": "Round 1, initiative order: Kira (7), Gorvek (5), Eirik (4 Player). Kira acts first. She will exploit Eirik's bold positioning to attack from cover, using her pre-rolled CREATURE ATTACKS d20 [20] for a shortbow shot with Sneak Attack (since Eirik is in melee threat range). Attack bonus +4 = 24 (automatic hit, potential critical). Damage: shortbow 1d6 [GENERIC DICE d6: 1] +2 DEX, plus Sneak Attack 1d6 [GENERIC DICE d6: 2]. Since it's a natural 20, both dice are rolled twice (crit). Shortbow: 1+1 = 2. Sneak Attack: 2+4 = 6. Total: 2 (base) + 2 (DEX) + 6 (Sneak) = 10 piercing, doubled on crit to 20 piercing (see standard rules: dice doubled, modifiers added once; total 2d6+2d6+2, or 4d6+2). After Kira's action, Gorvek will act and target Eirik, seeing him as the larger threat. Gorvek uses Multiattack: two attacks with scimitar, one with dagger (attack rolls: 14, 10, 5). After Gorvek, Eirik will act. Player will be prompted after Gorvek's turn.",
  "narration": "Your words hang in the smoky air, but Gorvek just laughs—a raw, ragged sound that echoes through the stronghold. 'Surrender? I've bled for every scrap in these woods. If you want me gone, you'll have to drag my corpse to the hills!'\n\nKira slips between the shifting shadows behind your broad form, arrow nocked and eyes narrowed. With you standing firm, she draws, exhales, and lets fly. The arrow arcs in a perfect, deadly line—a shot born of countless hours in the wild. It strikes Gorvek hard, piercing through his battered armor and biting deep near his collarbone. The force nearly drops the half-orc, blood spurting as he staggers, his eyes wide with pain and fury.\n\nRoaring in defiance, Gorvek charges at you. He swings his scimitar in a vicious arc—first strike, a blur of steel and fury, threatening to open your guard.",
  "combat_round": 1,
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateEncounter",
      "parameters": {
        "encounterId": "TW05-E1",
        "changes": "Bandit Captain Gorvek takes 20 piercing damage from Kira's critical shortbow Sneak Attack (HP 45 -> 25)."
      }
    },
    {
      "action": "updateCharacterInfo",
      "parameters": {
        "characterName": "scout_kira",
        "changes": "Fires one arrow from her shortbow, remaining hidden behind Eirik for cover."
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "plan": "Round 1 mid-cycle. Kira has completed her turn using a ranged attack (shortbow) with Sneak Attack—rogues at level 2 only have one attack per turn unless granted extra attacks by specific features, which Kira does not possess. Next in initiative: Bandit Captain Gorvek acts. He uses Multiattack: two scimitar attacks and one dagger attack against Eirik. His attack rolls (using CREATURE ATTACKS) are 14, 10, and 5. Scimitar attack 1: 14+5=19 (HIT vs AC 16). Scimitar attack 2: 10+5=15 (MISS). Dagger: 5+5=10 (MISS). Only the first scimitar hits. Damage: Scimitar 1d6 [GENERIC d6: 1] + 3 = 4 slashing. After Gorvek, it will be Eirik's turn.",
  "narration": "Kira, crouched in the shadows behind you, slips another arrow from her quiver, but her deadly precision is limited to a single shot each round—no flurry of arrows, just that one perfect strike. Rogues like her deal devastating damage with one attack, especially when an ally is close to the target, but they lack the relentless barrage of a trained fighter.\n\nBandit Captain Gorvek, howling in pain, barrels straight for you, Eirik. His scimitar flashes in a brutal arc, catching your side even as you raise your shield to parry—steel bites flesh, tearing through the scale mail with a jolt of pain. His second swing goes wide, glancing off your shield, and the dagger thrust that follows is turned aside by your armored arm. The bandit captain grins, sweat and blood streaming down his face, as he tries to press you back.\n\nKira calls out from behind, 'I’ve got your back, Eirik! Don’t let up!'\n\nGorvek’s attack leaves you wounded, but your stance is steady and your grip on the mace is strong. The initiative is yours. Gorvek just landed a hit with his first scimitar swing (4 slashing damage to you, HP 21 -> 17). The battlefield is lit by firelight, his corrupted armor gleaming and his breath coming in hard, angry bursts. Kira remains low and ready behind you. It’s your turn now, Eirik: you have 17/21 HP, you’re face-to-face with Gorvek, and Kira is close by. Your mace is ready—how do you strike back?",
  "combat_round": 1,
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateCharacterInfo",
      "parameters": {
        "characterName": "eirik_hearthwise",
        "changes": "Takes 4 slashing damage from Gorvek's first scimitar attack (HP reduced from 21 to 17)."
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "plan": "Round 1, Eirik's turn. Gorvek has just struck Eirik for 4 slashing (now 17/21 HP). Kira is nearby, having landed a devastating arrow. Eirik is in melee with Gorvek. Awaiting player attack roll: roll a d20 and add +4 (mace attack bonus). On a hit (target AC 15), roll 1d6+2 for bludgeoning damage. No advantage or disadvantage is in effect. After Eirik's turn, round 1 ends and initiative will return to Kira/top of the order.",
  "narration": "Blood seeps beneath your scale mail where Gorvek's blade found a gap, but you press forward, the weight of your mace familiar and reassuring in your grip. The half-orc bandit captain is breathing hard, fury in his eyes and fresh blood staining his armor from Kira's arrow, but he stands tall before you, daring you to come at him. Kira remains behind you, bow at the ready, eyes tracking every twitch of Gorvek's blade.\n\nThe firelight flickers over the embattled stronghold as you steel yourself and swing your mace, aiming for a decisive blow against your wounded foe.\n\nRoll a d20 and add your +4 attack bonus. If you hit AC 15, roll 1d6+2 for bludgeoning damage!",
  "combat_round": 1,
  "actions": []
}

{
  "plan": "Round 1 concludes. Eirik's attack roll of 15 matches Gorvek's AC (15), so the attack hits. Mace damage roll is 4 bludgeoning (2 on the die + 2 modifier). Gorvek's HP drops from 25 to 21. All creatures have now acted for round 1: Kira (ranged Sneak Attack critical), Gorvek (multiattack, one hit), Eirik (mace strike, 4 damage). Advance to combat_round 2. Initiative order returns to Kira at the top of the round.",
  "narration": "The blow lands solid—your mace smashes into Gorvek's armored ribs with a heavy, satisfying thud. He grunts and staggers to the side, the impact leaving a fresh dent in his battered mail and drawing another spatter of blood. For a moment, the half-orc looks ready to topple, but he squares himself, fighting through the pain, sweat and blood mingling on his brow.\n\nFirelight glints off the supernatural runes on his armor as he snarls, 'You hit like a priest, but I won't kneel to any god!'\n\nBehind you, Kira is already loosing her next arrow, darting for a new angle as you recover your guard. The fierce rhythm of battle surges on, with Gorvek wounded and wary but far from beaten.\n\nRound 2 begins. Kira is ready to strike again, her keen eyes searching for the smallest gap in Gorvek's defenses.",
  "combat_round": 2,
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateEncounter",
      "parameters": {
        "encounterId": "TW05-E1",
        "changes": "Bandit Captain Gorvek takes 4 bludgeoning damage from Eirik's mace attack (HP reduced from 25 to 21)."
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "plan": "Round 2, top of initiative. Order: Kira (7), Gorvek (5), Eirik (4 Player). Kira acts first. She attacks with her shortbow, using CREATURE ATTACKS d20 [1] + 6 = 7 (automatic miss, critical failure). Sneak Attack is not triggered. After Kira's attack, Gorvek will act: Multiattack (two scimitar, one dagger) with prerolled attack dice [7, 19, 7]. He will target Eirik, the visible threat. Attack 1: 7+5=12 (miss). Attack 2: 19+5=24 (hit). Dagger: 7+5=12 (miss). Only second scimitar hits. Damage for scimitar: 1d6 [GENERIC d6: 2] + 3 = 5 slashing. After Gorvek, it is Eirik's (player's) turn.",
  "narration": "As Gorvek recovers from your last blow, Kira slides along the edge of the firelight, drawing another arrow and sighting down her bow. You call out encouragement, but as she lets fly, the arrow glances off the haft of Gorvek's scimitar and vanishes into the darkness. Kira curses under her breath, frustration flickering across her face—her aim was true, but fate had other plans.\n\nWith a snarl, Gorvek seizes the opening. He barrels toward you, swinging his scimitar in a vicious pair of arcs. The first blow you catch on your shield, but the second slips past with brutal force, carving a deep furrow into your upper arm. You grit your teeth against the pain as his dagger thrust goes wide, missing you entirely.\n\nKira calls out, 'Sorry! He's moving too fast—I'll line up another shot!'\n\nYou stand your ground, blood streaking your arm but your resolve unbroken. The bandit captain is wounded and breathing hard, but his attacks are still deadly. The initiative is yours. Eirik, you have 12 out of 21 HP remaining, Gorvek stands directly before you with 21 HP, and Kira is nearby. The fire pit crackles behind you, casting wild shadows on the battered palisade. Your turn comes now—what is your next move?",
  "combat_round": 2,
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateCharacterInfo",
      "parameters": {
        "characterName": "eirik_hearthwise",
        "changes": "Takes 5 slashing damage from Gorvek's second scimitar attack (HP reduced from 17 to 12)."
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "plan": "Round 2, Eirik's turn. Gorvek has just wounded Eirik (now at 12/21 HP). Player declares Cure Wounds on self. This is a 1st-level spell, using 1 of 2 remaining L1 slots; after the spell, spell slots will be 1/3. Cure Wounds heals 1d8 + 3 (WIS mod), plus Disciple of Life adds 2+spell level (total +3), for a total bonus of +6. Player must roll 1d8 and add 6 to determine healing. No other actions occur until player's roll is resolved. After this, round 2 will end and initiative will return to Kira.",
  "narration": "As the pain from Gorvek's last strike throbs in your arm, you clutch your holy symbol and murmur a prayer to your patron. Radiant warmth flows through your body, knitting flesh and soothing the burning wound. The firelight seems to brighten for a heartbeat, driving back the shadow that clings to Gorvek's corrupted armor.\n\nKira glances over her shoulder, relief flickering in her eyes as she realizes you're still standing strong. Gorvek's face twists in confusion and then fury as he sees his foe healing mid-combat.\n\nRoll 1d8 and add 6 to determine how many hit points you recover from Cure Wounds.",
  "combat_round": 2,
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateCharacterInfo",
      "parameters": {
        "characterName": "eirik_hearthwise",
        "changes": "Expends one 1st-level spell slot to cast Cure Wounds on himself. Healing to be determined by player's roll (1d8 + 6)."
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "plan": "Round 2 resolution: Eirik cast Cure Wounds and healed for 10 HP, restoring from 12/21 HP up to his maximum of 21/21 HP (healing is capped at max HP). All creatures have taken their turns: Kira (attack missed), Gorvek (multiattack, 5 damage), Eirik (Cure Wounds, now fully healed). Advance combat_round to 3, initiative returns to Kira.",
  "narration": "Divine power surges from your holy symbol, flooding your wounds with gentle warmth. Bloodied skin knits together, bruises fade, and in moments you stand tall and unbroken—every injury erased by your faith and will. The pain is gone; you are whole again, a beacon of health among the firelit carnage.\n\nGorvek's eyes widen in disbelief as he sees your wounds vanish. 'I just cut you!' he snarls. Kira, emboldened by your miraculous recovery, darts to the side, seeking a new angle from which to break the captain's guard. The embers of the fire leap high, casting wild shadows as the fight continues.\n\nYou stand at your full strength, mace and shield ready, while Kira prepares to strike once more.\n\nRound 3 begins—Kira is first to act as the battle for the stronghold rages on.",
  "combat_round": 3,
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateCharacterInfo",
      "parameters": {
        "characterName": "eirik_hearthwise",
        "changes": "Cure Wounds restores 9 HP (healing capped at max HP), bringing Eirik to 21/21 HP."
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "plan": "Round 3, top of initiative. Kira acts first. She has one shortbow attack this round, using CREATURE ATTACKS d20 [18] + 6 = 24 (hit vs AC 15). Eirik is still engaged with Gorvek, so Sneak Attack applies. Damage: Shortbow 1d6 [GENERIC d6: 3] + 3 DEX = 6. Sneak Attack 1d6 [GENERIC d6: 1]. Total damage: 6 + 1 = 7 piercing. Gorvek's HP 21 -> 14. After Kira, Gorvek acts: Multiattack (scimitar, scimitar, dagger) with attack rolls [9, 12, 9]. He targets Eirik. Scimitar 1: 9+5=14 (miss). Scimitar 2: 12+5=17 (hit). Dagger: 9+5=14 (miss). Only the second scimitar hits. Damage: Scimitar 1d6 [GENERIC d6: 6] + 3 = 9 slashing. Eirik HP 21 -> 12. After Gorvek, Eirik's turn.",
  "narration": "Your words echo with the weight of true compassion, but Gorvek only sneers, his eyes wild with pain and pride. 'I am my own master!' he spits, steeling himself for another round of violence.\n\nKira, hearing your plea, hesitates just a heartbeat—then fires. Her arrow streaks through the smoky air and bites deep into Gorvek's thigh. He roars, staggering beneath the renewed assault, blood soaking the strange runes of his armor. 'Yield, Gorvek!' Kira calls, voice desperate. 'This doesn't have to end in ruin!'\n\nBut Gorvek is past hearing. With a guttural shout, he swings his blades at you again. The first is batted aside by your shield, but the second catches you in the side—a jolt of agony as steel parts flesh. His dagger whips past harmlessly, but the pain is real and sharp, and blood has begun to pool beneath your feet.\n\nThe fire pit flares behind, the stronghold lit by the chaos and heat of battle. Gorvek is wounded, bleeding from multiple wounds, but he stands defiant and dangerous. Kira looks to you, anxious, as you steady yourself for your next move.\n\nEirik, you have 12 out of 21 HP remaining, Gorvek stands at 14 HP, and Kira is at your back. The fate of the stronghold hangs in the balance. Your next action may end more than just the fight. What do you do?",
  "combat_round": 3,
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateEncounter",
      "parameters": {
        "encounterId": "TW05-E1",
        "changes": "Bandit Captain Gorvek takes 7 piercing damage from Kira's shortbow Sneak Attack (HP 21 -> 14)."
      }
    },
    {
      "action": "updateCharacterInfo",
      "parameters": {
        "characterName": "scout_kira",
        "changes": "Fires another arrow, landing a solid hit from behind Eirik."
      }
    },
    {
      "action": "updateCharacterInfo",
      "parameters": {
        "characterName": "eirik_hearthwise",
        "changes": "Takes 9 slashing damage from Gorvek's second scimitar attack (HP reduced from 21 to 12)."
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "plan": "Round 3, Eirik's turn. All actions for this round except Eirik's have been resolved: Kira struck Gorvek for 7 damage (Gorvek HP now 14), Gorvek hit Eirik for 9 damage (Eirik HP now 12). Spell slots correction: Eirik has 1 first-level slot remaining (not zero), as only two 1st-level spells have been cast. Initiative order is Kira -> Gorvek -> Eirik (Player), so it is now the player's turn.",
  "narration": "You steady yourself as Gorvek's latest strike leaves your side burning, blood running beneath your armor. Despite his wounds and the desperate pleas, the half-orc captain refuses to yield, lashing out with a strength born of pride and desperation. Kira remains vigilant behind you, watching for the next opening, her last arrow having struck true.\n\nYou have one spell slot left, your faith and strength both undiminished. The embers of the fire pit spark behind Gorvek, shadows flickering across his battered, rune-marked armor. He stands on the edge of defeat, his breath ragged, but there's murder in his eyes.\n\nHere is your tactical snapshot:\n- Gorvek just struck you for 9 damage (you have 12/21 HP left). He now stands bloodied at 14 HP.\n- Kira's arrow left him limping.\n- Your remaining spell slots: 1/3 (level 1).\n- The battlefield is tight, with Kira at your back and the central fire pit casting all movement in wild shadows.\n\nThe stronghold’s fate may hinge on your next action. Your mace is slick with blood, your shield battered. Will you stand firm, heal once more, or try something desperate? The choice is yours. What do you do?",
  "combat_round": 3,
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateCharacterInfo",
      "parameters": {
        "characterName": "eirik_hearthwise",
        "changes": "Restores spell slot count to 1 remaining at first level, correcting previous error."
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "plan": "Round 3, Eirik's turn. All enemies have acted. Eirik (Player) is attacking Gorvek with his mace. Awaiting player's attack roll: roll a d20 and add +4 (mace attack bonus). Target AC is 15. On a hit, roll 1d6+2 for bludgeoning damage. No advantage or disadvantage applies. After resolution, round 3 will end and initiative will return to Kira for round 4.",
  "narration": "You ignore the pulse of pain and let your training take over. Gorvek is reeling, blood from Kira's arrow soaking his leg, but his scimitars are still deadly close. The stronghold's fire crackles behind him, casting his shadow long and wild across the battered ground. Kira calls encouragement—her next arrow already halfway drawn.\n\nYou tighten your grip, step forward, and swing your mace in a forceful arc, aiming to break through the captain's defenses and end this brutal duel.\n\nRoll a d20 and add your +4 attack bonus. If your total equals or beats Gorvek's AC of 15, roll 1d6+2 for bludgeoning damage!",
  "combat_round": 3,
  "actions": []
}

{
  "plan": "Round 3, Eirik's turn concludes. Player's attack roll of 18 is a solid hit against Gorvek's AC 15. Damage is 4+2=6 bludgeoning. Gorvek HP drops from 14 to 8. All creatures have acted this round: Kira (shortbow hit, 7 damage), Gorvek (multiattack, 9 damage to Eirik), Eirik (mace hit, 6 damage). Advance to combat_round 4. Initiative returns to Kira.",
  "narration": "Your mace connects with a brutal crunch, smashing into Gorvek's side and sending him stumbling. He spits blood, snarling as his knees nearly buckle. The enchanted runes on his battered armor gutter and flicker, dimming under the combined onslaught. For a heartbeat, you see fear in his eyes—he knows he's running out of time.\n\nKira, now fully emboldened by your blow, nocks her next arrow and calls out, 'He’s faltering, Eirik! I’ll pin him down—finish this!'\n\nThe stronghold quakes with the crackle of fire and the furious clamor of battle. Gorvek stands swaying, blood pouring from a half-dozen wounds, but his grip on his weapons remains tight. The fight is nearly at its end, the next few heartbeats sure to decide the fate of the bandit lord.\n\nRound 4 begins. Kira is first to act, ready to press the advantage.",
  "combat_round": 4,
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateEncounter",
      "parameters": {
        "encounterId": "TW05-E1",
        "changes": "Bandit Captain Gorvek takes 6 bludgeoning damage from Eirik's mace attack (HP 14 -> 8)."
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "plan": "Round 4, top of initiative. Kira acts first. Eirik attempts to persuade Gorvek to surrender, but Gorvek's personality, supernatural corruption, and current state make surrender highly unlikely in the heat of battle. Kira, hearing Eirik's plea, gives Gorvek a chance to yield but stays ready. Using CREATURE ATTACKS d20 [10] + 6 = 16 (hit vs AC 15) for shortbow attack if Gorvek refuses. Gorvek will respond with defiance and violence, then Kira fires. Damage: shortbow 1d6 [GENERIC d6: 2] + 3 = 5. Sneak Attack 1d6 [GENERIC d6: 2] (Eirik is adjacent for Sneak Attack). Total: 5 + 2 = 7 piercing. Gorvek HP 8 -> 1. Next: Gorvek acts, Multiattack (scimitar, scimitar, dagger) using prerolled attack rolls [5, 20, 1]. Scimitar 1: 5+5=10 (miss); Scimitar 2: 20+5=25 (critical hit). Dagger: 1+5=6 (miss). Crit damage: scimitar 2d6 [GENERIC d6: 4, 1] + 3 = 8 slashing. Eirik HP 12 -> 4. After Gorvek, it is Eirik's turn.",
  "narration": "Your voice rings out again, heavy with conviction. 'I grant you one last chance at life. Surrender, Gorvek!'\n\nFor a split second, the battered half-orc pauses, eyes darting to the blood leaking from his wounds, then to the flames, then to the battered remnants of his stronghold. But the supernatural green light flickers in his gaze, and he grits his tusked teeth. 'I’ll die before I kneel!' he spits, voice ragged with pain and defiance.\n\nKira, hearing your plea and seeing Gorvek's stubborn resolve, nods grimly. 'You heard him, Eirik.' She looses another arrow, and this one strikes deep—burying itself in Gorvek’s side, nearly toppling him. He staggers, now barely standing, blood pouring onto the blackened ground.\n\nWith a furious, final roar, Gorvek launches himself at you. His first wild swing misses entirely, but then his eyes flash with unnatural fury and a critical blow slips under your guard, the blade biting deep into your side. You gasp as pain blossoms, nearly dropping to one knee, but you hold fast—his dagger misses as he overextends.\n\nKira shouts, 'Eirik, end it! He’s barely standing!'\n\nYou grip your shield tight, vision swimming for a heartbeat. The stronghold is silent except for the crackle of fire and Gorvek’s ragged breathing. You have 4 HP remaining. Gorvek, battered and defiant, is clinging to life with 1 HP. Your next blow may decide it all. What do you do?",
  "combat_round": 4,
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateEncounter",
      "parameters": {
        "encounterId": "TW05-E1",
        "changes": "Bandit Captain Gorvek takes 7 piercing damage from Kira's shortbow Sneak Attack (HP 8 -> 1)."
      }
    },
    {
      "action": "updateCharacterInfo",
      "parameters": {
        "characterName": "scout_kira",
        "changes": "Fires another arrow, striking Gorvek with deadly precision."
      }
    },
    {
      "action": "updateCharacterInfo",
      "parameters": {
        "characterName": "eirik_hearthwise",
        "changes": "Takes 8 slashing damage from Gorvek's critical scimitar attack (HP 12 -> 4)."
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "plan": "Round 4, Eirik's turn. Gorvek is at 1 HP, Eirik at 4 HP. Awaiting player's attack roll with mace: roll a d20 and add +4 (attack bonus). Target AC is 15. On a hit, roll 1d6+2 for bludgeoning damage. No advantage/disadvantage. If Gorvek is reduced to 0 HP, encounter will end after resolving the blow. Otherwise, round advances to 5 and initiative returns to Kira.",
  "narration": "You steel yourself, fighting through searing pain. Gorvek stands before you—barely upright, bloodied, and defiant, his weapons trembling in exhausted hands. Kira's arrow juts from his side, and his breathing is ragged, but the murderous light in his eyes hasn't faded. The fire pit flickers behind him, illuminating the battered stronghold in hellish gold.\n\nOne last time, you raise your mace and bring it down, determined to finish this fight—one way or another.\n\nRoll a d20 for your attack and add your +4 bonus. If you hit AC 15, roll 1d6+2 for the damage that may end Gorvek’s reign for good!",
  "combat_round": 4,
  "actions": []
}

{
  "plan": "Round 4, Eirik's attack roll of 18 is a solid hit against Gorvek's AC 15. Player must now roll 1d6+2 for bludgeoning damage. Gorvek is at 1 HP; any hit will drop him. Await damage roll confirmation from player. After this, Gorvek will be defeated and the encounter will conclude.",
  "narration": "You bring your mace around in a final, desperate arc. The battered captain, blood and sweat pouring down his face, tries to raise his blade in one last defense—but your resolve is greater. The head of your mace is on target.\n\nYou've landed a solid blow against Gorvek's battered form. Now, roll 1d6 and add 2 to see if you finish the bandit captain once and for all!",
  "combat_round": 4,
  "actions": []
}

{
  "plan": "Round 4, Eirik's mace connects for 2+2=4 bludgeoning damage, dropping Gorvek from 1 HP to -3 HP. Gorvek is defeated and falls in the stronghold's firelight. All creatures in the initiative have now acted; the encounter is over. Advance combat_round to 5 and trigger the exit action after describing the scene.",
  "narration": "Your mace smashes into Gorvek's jaw with a dull, final crack. The bandit captain's eyes widen in shock, the green corruption in his gaze guttering out. He drops his scimitars, staggers once, and crashes onto his knees. For one last, flickering heartbeat, he locks eyes with you—rage, pride, and a desperate, unspoken plea mingling in his battered face. Then Gorvek slumps forward onto the blood-soaked earth, the firelight painting his fallen form in flickering gold and shadow.\n\nKira lowers her bow, breath trembling in her chest. For a moment, the stronghold is eerily quiet, save for the snapping of flames and the pounding of your own heart.\n\nThe corrupted reign of Bandit Captain Gorvek is ended. The Thornwood Wilds are free of his grip—at least for now.",
  "combat_round": 5,
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateEncounter",
      "parameters": {
        "encounterId": "TW05-E1",
        "changes": "Bandit Captain Gorvek takes 4 bludgeoning damage from Eirik's mace and is now dead (HP 1 -> -3)."
      }
    },
    {
      "action": "exit",
      "parameters": {}
    }
  ]
}
